This paper discusses the characteristics of people's collections of web pages and their needs for a system to manage their web-based distributed collections. The study involves examining user practices and problems in maintaining their web-based collections. This work is relevant to several sub-categories, including Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC), Information Retrieval (cs.IR), Digital Libraries (cs.DL), Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), and Computation and Language (cs.CL).
